itecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/...\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"id\": \"item_32\", \"text\": \"Added the project charter docs at [README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md), [docs/product-brief.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md), and [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md). The README now calls out the past-sessions-first home screen early, lists the full staged workflow in order, and documents the fixed stack and local development expectations. The architecture note records the backend-only Gemini boundary and the requirement for resumable server-side composition/audio jobs.\\n\\nVerification was docs-focused: I manually reviewed all three files, ran a Python acceptance check covering file presence, first-screen wording, ordered workflow, fixed stack documentation, backend Gemini rationale, resumable jobs rationale, and sessions-home coverage in the product brief, and ran `git diff --check`, which passed. No tests, builds, browser checks, or screenshots were applicable because this task was documentation-only.\\n\\nI created the requested checkpoint commit `feat(prompt-00): project charter`, and the required reviewer summary file was written last at [prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md).\", \"type\": \"agent_message\"}, \"type\": \"item.completed\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 62, \"prompt_index\": 1, \"prompt_name\": \"00 \\u2014 Project Charter and Success Criteria\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"timestap\": \"2026-03-31T20:59:05-07:00\"}\n./prompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.jsonlines:63:{\"color\": \"bright_black\", \"emoji\": \"\\u2753\", \"event_type\": \"Unkown Event\", \"message\": \"{ \\\"item\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"item_15\\\", \\\"items\\\": [ { \\\"completed\\\": true, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Draft top-level README with product vision, ordered workflow, fixed technology decisions, and local development expectations\\\" }, { \\\"completed\\\": true, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Add docs...\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"id\": \"item_15\", \"items\": [{\"completed\": true, \"text\": \"Draft top-level README with product vision, ordered workflow, fixed technology decisions, and local development expectations\"}, {\"completed\": true, \"text\": \"Add docs/product-brief.md and docs/architecture-overview.md aligned to the prompt and current scaffold\"}, {\"completed\": false, \"text\": \"Verify content against acceptance criteria, commit a checkpoint, and write prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md as the final action\"}], \"type\": \"todo_list\"}, \"type\": \"item.completed\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 63, \"prompt_index\": 1, \"prompt_name\": \"00 \\u2014 Project Charter and Success Criteria\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"timestap\": \"2026-03-31T20:59:05-07:00\"}\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:11:  - Called out the first-screen requirement in the opening paragraph: the app starts from a past-sessions view for resume, edit, and create flows.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:12:  - Listed the required story workflow in order from genre selection through finalize/read/listen/download.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:18:  - Captured the bedtime-story positioning, the sessions-first UX requirement, the staged workflow, the two-pane workspace, and the chat/UI bridge rules.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:23:  - Explained why composition and audio must run as resumable server-side jobs backed by durable state.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:43:  - PostgreSQL-backed job records, segment records, and event logs are part of the intended design.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:56:  - Example: if you are implementing the sessions home screen later, the README makes it explicit that this is the first meaningful screen and not a secondary route.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:58:- Use `docs/product-brief.md` when making UX or workflow decisions.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:59:  - Example: if you are building pitch generation or beat-sheet editing, the product brief defines the required stage order and the expectation that chat and UI actions mirror each other.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:62:  - Example: if you later add composition workers, this doc already sets the expectation that they persist progress server-side and do not stream from ephemeral request state.\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:80:- `past_sessions_called_out_early`: `True`\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:81:- `workflow_listed_in_order`: `True`\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:85:- `product_brief_has_sessions_home`: `True`\n./prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:126:- `git status` also showed Yolopilot-generated prompt artifact files under `prompts/`. I did not include those in the checkpoint commit because they were workflow artifacts, not part of the requested deliverables.\n./prompts/98-demo-data-and-onboarding.md:7:Make the app easier to explore by providing seeded demo sessions or an onboarding hint flow for new developers and first-time users.\n./prompts/98-demo-data-and-onboarding.md:10:- Create optional demo data that shows at least one in-progress session and one completed session with representative metadata.\n./prompts/98-demo-data-and-onboarding.md:11:- Add a light onboarding empty state on the home screen that explains the workflow in plain language.\n./prompts/98-demo-data-and-onboarding.md:23:- The home screen is informative even when no sessions exist.\n./prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md:12:- Split the code into sensible modules such as settings, api routes, db, services, and domain models.\n./prompts/27-reusable-form-and-card-components.md:22:- Future prompts can compose the workflow from reusable parts rather than one-off markup.\n./prompts/27-reusable-form-and-card-components.md:28:Build just enough system to accelerate the workflow screens.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:7:Implement the first product-facing screen: a page where the user can see prior story sessions, tell whether they are in progress or complete, and resume or start fresh.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:10:- Build a backend endpoint that lists recent sessions with key metadata like title, last modified time, stage, and completion status.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:11:- Create the home screen UI that renders these sessions in a useful list or card layout and includes a strong ‘new session’ action.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:22:- A user lands on the past-sessions screen first, not on a blank editor.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:23:- Both in-progress and completed sessions are clearly distinguishable.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:24:- The user can enter an existing session or start a new one from this screen.\n./prompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md:32:`feat(prompt-21): past sessions home screen`\n./prompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.md:10:- Add integration tests for migrations, session creation, event logging, asset metadata, and job claiming.\n./prompts/33-action-echoes-in-chat.md:23:- A resumed session can show how a key choice was made even if it was made in the UI rather than typed.\n./frontend/README.md:24:Later prompts should extend this TypeScript app into the sessions-first workspace rather than replacing it.\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:5:I replaced the placeholder JSX frontend with a real Vite React TypeScript foundation and kept the repo aligned with the product direction from `base_prompt.md`: Storyteller should be a sessions-first bedtime-story studio, not a generic demo page.\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:22:  - The page now communicates “past sessions come first”.\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:23:  - The route previews the intended workflow stages without pretending the real product flow exists yet.\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:52:### Frontend composition now has clear layers\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:86:import { SessionsRoute } from '../features/sessions/SessionsRoute.tsx'\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:94:      { path: 'sessions/:sessionId', element: <SessionsRoute /> },\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:190:  - presence of the sessions-first copy\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:267:  - `Past sessions come first` text rendered\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:338:- I assumed the placeholder landing screen should already reflect the product contract that “past sessions” is the first meaningful screen, even though real session data is not in scope yet. I therefore used static preview content rather than a generic marketing hero or a raw empty shell.\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:348:- The home route is still a static placeholder. It does not yet read sessions, call real frontend APIs beyond `/api/hello`, or implement the two-pane workspace.\n./prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md:350:- There is only one unit test file so far. That is appropriate for the current scaffold stage, but future prompts should expand test coverage as real routing, state, and API clients appear.\n./backend/app/storage/status.py:11:            settings.gcs_bucket_names.sessions,\n./prompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.codex.jsonlines:8:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_3\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc 'rg --files'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"prompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines\\nprompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md\\nprompts/99-release-checklist-and-future-roadmap.md\\nprompts/44-pitch-generation-pipeline.md\\nprompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.codex.jsonlines\\nprompts/42-story-setup-brief-form.md\\nprompts/07-developer-bootstrap-scripts.md\\nprompts/20